Traditional woodworking refers to furniture making techniques that rely on hand tools, joinery and detailed knowledge of wood as a natural material.

Before the introduction of industrial machines, furniture was built using tools such as hand planes, chisels, saws and marking gauges. Craftsmen developed joints like dovetails and mortise and tenon connections that allowed furniture to remain structurally stable for generations.

Today traditional woodworking is still practiced by furniture makers and craft workshops that focus on durable construction and material awareness. At Bensari Workshop in Wrocław these techniques are taught through practical woodworking courses and applied in contemporary furniture making.
